The previous attempt failed primarily because it referenced an unknown identifier `ComplexMeasure.integral_add_measure`. By relying on the general `map_add` lemma (which applies to bundled linear and additive maps) and simplifying the definitions of the measures and functionals involved, we can show that the integral of a function against a measure associated with $x + y$ is the sum of the integrals associated with $x$ and $y$ separately.

